sentences: Nalini "Deedee" Cheriel is a visual artist, musician and filmmaker who lives in Los Angeles, California.
From the age of 19, Cheriel started out creating record covers and T-shirts for the Oregon music scene.
In 2001, Cheriel, along with friends Kurt Voss and Zoe Poledouris, created the film Down and Out With the Dolls.
After this film was released, Cheriel moved to Los Angeles, California where she lives still.
After moving to Los Angeles, Cheriel began work as a visual artist.
